1
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:09,250
Hey! Don't change that channel!

2
00:00:09,333 --> 00:00:12,041
You don't wanna miss
a second of this one!

3
00:00:12,125 --> 00:00:13,833
An heiress who can
assess a man's value

4
00:00:13,916 --> 00:00:15,458
has her eyes on yours truly.

5
00:00:15,541 --> 00:00:18,500
Today's lesson will be about
discovering your "self-worth."

6
00:00:18,583 --> 00:00:20,291
All teachers are looking
for diamonds in the rough,

7
00:00:20,375 --> 00:00:23,458
and I, Junichiro Kagami,
the Ultimate Otaku Teacher,

8
00:00:23,541 --> 00:00:25,333
always find them first!

9
00:01:54,541 --> 00:01:58,208
[MADOKA] My, my.
Nothing but pocket change.

10
00:01:58,291 --> 00:02:00,875
Is there really no
man worth his salt?

11
00:02:00,958 --> 00:02:04,791
I've seen more dollar signs
between the sofa cushions.

12
00:02:04,875 --> 00:02:05,833
Hmm...

13
00:02:08,166 --> 00:02:10,333
Although, I guess
that's to be expected.

14
00:02:10,416 --> 00:02:13,291
When supply is high,
demand will be low.

15
00:02:18,708 --> 00:02:19,625
[SOCCER PLAYER  A]
I can't hear you!

16
00:02:19,708 --> 00:02:21,666
[SOCCER PLAYERS]
Yeah!

17
00:02:21,750 --> 00:02:24,375
[MALE ICHO SOCCER PLAYERS]
One, two! One, two! Fight on!

18
00:02:24,458 --> 00:02:26,250
Fight on! One, two...

19
00:02:26,333 --> 00:02:29,750
[JUNICHIRO groans]

20
00:02:29,833 --> 00:02:33,791
--[stomach growls]
--[groaning continues]

21
00:02:40,625 --> 00:02:42,083
[sighs]

22
00:02:42,166 --> 00:02:44,291
[JUNICHIRO] Three weeks ago,
I managed to convince Suzune

23
00:02:44,375 --> 00:02:45,458
to start giving me lunch money

24
00:02:45,541 --> 00:02:47,958
instead of making me
brown bag every day.

25
00:02:48,041 --> 00:02:48,958
Little does she know,

26
00:02:49,041 --> 00:02:50,500
I've actually been
saving the cash

27
00:02:50,583 --> 00:02:52,125
and getting by on just water.

28
00:02:52,208 --> 00:02:53,375
[chuckles]

29
00:02:53,458 --> 00:02:54,750
[JUNICHIRO]
But that ends today,

30
00:02:54,833 --> 00:02:56,666
because I've finally
saved up enough money

31
00:02:56,750 --> 00:02:59,708
to snag me a copy
of Battle World 3!

32
00:02:59,791 --> 00:03:01,791
[MUSCLE CLUB LEADER]
Yo! You can't do me like that!

33
00:03:01,875 --> 00:03:03,041
[JUNICHIRO]
Hm?

34
00:03:03,125 --> 00:03:04,125
[MADOKA]
Complain all you like,

35
00:03:04,208 --> 00:03:06,000
but you're not
getting another cent.

36
00:03:06,083 --> 00:03:07,541
Dude, what?

37
00:03:07,625 --> 00:03:09,458
But that's cutting the Muscle
Adventure Club's budget by,

38
00:03:09,541 --> 00:03:11,625
like, ninety percent
or something, right?

39
00:03:11,708 --> 00:03:13,083
Well I'm impressed.

40
00:03:13,166 --> 00:03:15,708
I didn't know you could do
math like that in your head!

41
00:03:15,791 --> 00:03:17,291
Of course, it doesn't
change the fact

42
00:03:17,375 --> 00:03:20,250
that you yourself are only
worth six-fifty, little boy!

43
00:03:20,333 --> 00:03:21,666
[gasps]
What?

44
00:03:21,750 --> 00:03:23,541
'Kay, gang, can I
help who's next?

45
00:03:23,625 --> 00:03:25,750
Bro, she ain't serious
with this, right?

46
00:03:25,833 --> 00:03:27,125
Well that was nice.

47
00:03:27,208 --> 00:03:28,916
Ever heard of tact, Kuramochi?

48
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:31,083
Hey, I wasn't trying to be ugly.

49
00:03:31,166 --> 00:03:33,333
I was just giving
them their flat rate.

50
00:03:33,416 --> 00:03:35,166
Don't be so stuffy!

51
00:03:35,250 --> 00:03:38,416
What? "Stuffy?" "Flat rate?"

52
00:03:38,500 --> 00:03:40,708
[JUNICHIRO]
Hey, Twin-Tails weirdo!

53
00:03:40,791 --> 00:03:43,333
Great. What are you doing here?

54
00:03:43,416 --> 00:03:45,458
I work here. Who's she?

55
00:03:45,541 --> 00:03:46,958
[MAKINA grunts]

56
00:03:47,041 --> 00:03:49,041
[MAKINA]
Her name's Madoka Kuramochi.

57
00:03:49,125 --> 00:03:51,291
She has a talent for
determining the net worth

58
00:03:51,375 --> 00:03:53,958
of anything she
looks at on the fly.

59
00:03:54,041 --> 00:03:56,875
That includes people,
just so you know.

60
00:03:56,958 --> 00:03:59,208
Sounds like a big
shot naming a bounty.

61
00:03:59,291 --> 00:04:01,583
She's been a big help
to the student council.

62
00:04:01,666 --> 00:04:03,083
It may seem a little cold,

63
00:04:03,166 --> 00:04:05,541
but she's never given out a
budget that's gone to waste.

64
00:04:05,625 --> 00:04:07,500
Despite only being
in her first year,

65
00:04:07,583 --> 00:04:10,208
she's already our
full-time accountant.

66
00:04:10,291 --> 00:04:13,125
And one day she'll inherit
her family's company.

67
00:04:13,208 --> 00:04:14,708
She's hacked.

68
00:04:14,791 --> 00:04:16,833
There's no way to have such high
character stats without cheats.

69
00:04:16,916 --> 00:04:20,500
Well... I don't think that
means her life is easy.

70
00:04:20,583 --> 00:04:22,833
[gasps] Wait, you only
teach part-time.

71
00:04:22,916 --> 00:04:25,583
If you don't have a class, why
are you just hanging around?

72
00:04:25,666 --> 00:04:27,166
Oh, uh...

73
00:04:27,250 --> 00:04:30,000
Actually, I was hoping I could
find someone to buy me lunch.

74
00:04:30,083 --> 00:04:31,291
[stomach growls]

75
00:04:31,375 --> 00:04:32,791
You bum!

76
00:04:32,875 --> 00:04:34,833
You can't extort your students
into getting food for you!

77
00:04:34,916 --> 00:04:37,000
No way! Not on my watch!

78
00:04:37,083 --> 00:04:38,666
Mr. Kagami!

79
00:04:38,750 --> 00:04:40,208
Whoa! Deep breaths!

80
00:04:40,291 --> 00:04:41,291
[gasps]

81
00:04:41,375 --> 00:04:42,500
[MADOKA]
What'd she say?

82
00:04:42,583 --> 00:04:44,916
You call yourself
a teacher?

83
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:45,750
Leave!

84
00:04:45,833 --> 00:04:46,833
[yelps]

85
00:04:46,916 --> 00:04:48,875
[MAKINA] You can
buy your own lunches!

86
00:04:48,958 --> 00:04:51,333
[MADOKA]
So he's Junichiro Kagami.

87
00:04:51,416 --> 00:04:52,666
Interesting.

88
00:04:54,875 --> 00:04:56,041
[JUNICHIRO]
Da na na na!

89
00:04:56,125 --> 00:04:57,458
The wait is over!

90
00:04:57,541 --> 00:04:59,583
Man, it sure feels
satisfying to buy something

91
00:04:59,666 --> 00:05:00,958
with my hard-earned money!

92
00:05:01,041 --> 00:05:03,666
[laughing]
All right!

93
00:05:05,166 --> 00:05:08,416
[JUNICHIRO]
Heh? Oh, cool, a flea market.

94
00:05:08,500 --> 00:05:11,625
Wonder if there's anything
worth my spare change?

95
00:05:14,208 --> 00:05:14,833
[JUNICHIRO]
Huh?

96
00:05:14,916 --> 00:05:17,375
[gasps]

97
00:05:17,458 --> 00:05:18,791
Whoa!

98
00:05:18,875 --> 00:05:20,875
Sergeant Saunders in Close
Combat Mode is a must buy!

99
00:05:20,958 --> 00:05:23,416
You may consider this
one purchased, my man!

100
00:05:23,500 --> 00:05:24,541
[MERCHANT]
Nice choice!

101
00:05:24,625 --> 00:05:26,666
[MADOKA]
Now, let's not be hasty!

102
00:05:26,750 --> 00:05:29,375
You don't mind if I give this
doll a once over, do you?

103
00:05:29,458 --> 00:05:31,541
I, uh, suppose that's
not a problem.

104
00:05:31,625 --> 00:05:33,458
She's so cute!

105
00:05:33,541 --> 00:05:34,666
What a shame.

106
00:05:34,750 --> 00:05:37,333
She comes at such an
unreasonably high price.

107
00:05:37,416 --> 00:05:38,958
Nuh-uh, it's a steal.

108
00:05:39,041 --> 00:05:40,500
That's a limited edition--

109
00:05:40,583 --> 00:05:42,041
--[MADOKA] Up!
--[gasps]

110
00:05:42,125 --> 00:05:44,583
She just took her innocence!

111
00:05:44,666 --> 00:05:45,625
Huh?

112
00:05:47,375 --> 00:05:48,750
Well, sir.

113
00:05:48,833 --> 00:05:52,750
She's looking a tad rough
right around the lady parts.

114
00:05:52,833 --> 00:05:55,000
Uh-uh...

115
00:05:55,083 --> 00:05:57,291
How can this be?

116
00:05:58,750 --> 00:06:00,041
[JUNICHIRO]
Thanks for catching that.

117
00:06:00,125 --> 00:06:03,166
I'd have hated buying
something that was damaged.

118
00:06:03,250 --> 00:06:04,875
Plus, that guy was
so embarrassed,

119
00:06:04,958 --> 00:06:06,750
he gave me a better discount.

120
00:06:06,833 --> 00:06:08,583
[MADOKA]
It wasn't a big deal.

121
00:06:08,666 --> 00:06:09,666
No, I owe you.

122
00:06:09,750 --> 00:06:11,083
How can I pay you back?

123
00:06:11,166 --> 00:06:12,666
Let's see.

124
00:06:12,750 --> 00:06:15,833
I suppose if you're offering,
today is my sixteenth birthday.

125
00:06:15,916 --> 00:06:17,625
Really? You don't say.

126
00:06:17,708 --> 00:06:18,958
Well, in that case,

127
00:06:19,041 --> 00:06:21,041
if there's something I
can give you, it's yours.

128
00:06:21,125 --> 00:06:22,125
[MADOKA]
Hmm...

129
00:06:24,083 --> 00:06:25,041
Huh?

130
00:06:26,250 --> 00:06:28,583
The only thing
I want is you.

131
00:06:28,666 --> 00:06:30,333
Huh?

132
00:06:30,416 --> 00:06:33,375
Way to make it weird.
Ugh. I'm out.

133
00:06:35,583 --> 00:06:37,500
Whoa! Stop right there!

134
00:06:37,583 --> 00:06:38,541
[JUNICHIRO grunts]

135
00:06:40,666 --> 00:06:42,708
Are you trying to
get away from me?

136
00:06:44,666 --> 00:06:45,625
[grunts]

137
00:06:48,833 --> 00:06:50,208
--[MADOKA gasps]
--[JUNICHIRO laughs]

138
00:06:50,291 --> 00:06:51,708
You think people
would know by now,

139
00:06:51,791 --> 00:06:53,541
no one can catch
me in Akihabara!

140
00:06:53,625 --> 00:06:55,083
Get back here!

141
00:06:55,166 --> 00:06:56,291
[JUNISHIRO chuckles]

142
00:06:56,375 --> 00:06:58,041
[MADOKA]
Stop running!

143
00:06:58,125 --> 00:06:59,208
[JUNICHIRO]
Yeah, right!

144
00:06:59,291 --> 00:07:00,500
[MADOKA pants]

145
00:07:00,583 --> 00:07:02,125
[JUNICHIRO pants]

146
00:07:04,083 --> 00:07:05,625
[MADOKA breathes heavily]

147
00:07:07,041 --> 00:07:08,958
[JUNICHIRO]
Heh? Hmm...

148
00:07:10,250 --> 00:07:11,791
[JUNICHIRO]
Finally lost her.

149
00:07:13,208 --> 00:07:15,666
That girl sure had
an odd request.

150
00:07:15,750 --> 00:07:17,208
What would she want me for?

151
00:07:17,291 --> 00:07:19,208
[MUSCLE CLUB LEADER]
Found you, prima dona!

152
00:07:19,291 --> 00:07:20,666
[MUSCLE CLUB MEMBER A]
We need to talk!

153
00:07:20,750 --> 00:07:22,333
[MUSCLE CLUB MEMBER B]
Yeah, what he said!

154
00:07:22,416 --> 00:07:23,916
[JUNICHIRO]
Not good.

155
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:25,666
[MUSCLE CLUB LEADER]
Thanks to you, we can't afford

156
00:07:25,750 --> 00:07:28,583
protein shakes or
haircuts no more.

157
00:07:28,666 --> 00:07:30,958
And you're gonna pay for that.

158
00:07:32,583 --> 00:07:34,666
Wow, turned a phrase.

159
00:07:34,750 --> 00:07:37,208
Unfortunately, that's not
nearly enough to help you

160
00:07:37,291 --> 00:07:38,958
with your monetary concerns.

161
00:07:39,041 --> 00:07:41,666
See, it's your bad attitude
that made your price low.

162
00:07:41,750 --> 00:07:42,916
[growls]

163
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:44,416
[MADOKA gasps]

164
00:07:44,500 --> 00:07:46,291
[MUSCLE CLUB LEADER]
You got an awful big mouth

165
00:07:46,375 --> 00:07:48,375
for someone so small.

166
00:07:48,458 --> 00:07:49,833
So I'm gonna shut it!

167
00:07:49,916 --> 00:07:51,000
[gasps]

168
00:07:51,083 --> 00:07:52,375
[yells]

169
00:07:52,458 --> 00:07:53,416
[JUNICHIRO grunts]

170
00:07:54,416 --> 00:07:56,166
[gasps]

171
00:07:56,250 --> 00:07:58,125
[MUSCLE CLUB LEADER]
What the hell is this?

172
00:07:58,208 --> 00:07:59,666
--[JUNICHIRO grunts]
--[MADOKA whimpers]

173
00:07:59,750 --> 00:08:00,625
Heh.

174
00:08:00,708 --> 00:08:03,333
[OTAKU A gasps]
Mitsuki-chan!

175
00:08:03,416 --> 00:08:05,000
Where art thou?

176
00:08:05,083 --> 00:08:06,666
[gasps]
Huh?

177
00:08:06,750 --> 00:08:09,666
We saw on social media a
famous cosplayer was gonna be

178
00:08:09,750 --> 00:08:12,500
doing a photoshoot in
this creepy back alley!

179
00:08:12,583 --> 00:08:14,750
That is why
you're here, isn't it?

180
00:08:14,833 --> 00:08:16,958
No, we're here for...

181
00:08:17,041 --> 00:08:18,583
What?

182
00:08:18,666 --> 00:08:19,666
They're gone!

183
00:08:19,750 --> 00:08:20,666
[MUSCLE CLUB MEMBER B]
Where'd they go?

184
00:08:20,750 --> 00:08:25,250
[BOTH pant]

185
00:08:25,333 --> 00:08:26,750
Only took the
otaku-razzi

186
00:08:26,833 --> 00:08:29,000
three minutes to get there
after I made that post.

187
00:08:29,083 --> 00:08:31,708
I guess they bring new meaning
to the phrase "gotta go fast!"

188
00:08:31,791 --> 00:08:33,416
Still cut it close, though.

189
00:08:33,500 --> 00:08:35,291
I guess I owe you now
after that save--

190
00:08:35,375 --> 00:08:38,458
[screams]

191
00:08:38,541 --> 00:08:41,916
Oh! My copy of Battle World 3
is in a million pieces now!

192
00:08:42,000 --> 00:08:43,708
[MADOKA]
Is it really worth crying over?

193
00:08:43,791 --> 00:08:44,666
Of course!

194
00:08:44,750 --> 00:08:46,250
This game is made by KMC,

195
00:08:46,333 --> 00:08:48,541
the fastest-growing video
game developer in Japan

196
00:08:48,625 --> 00:08:50,541
because they're known for
going against the grain!

197
00:08:50,625 --> 00:08:52,833
FPS games are mostly
from Western companies.

198
00:08:52,916 --> 00:08:54,750
KMC is the only
Japanese publisher

199
00:08:54,833 --> 00:08:56,750
to have any significance
in that genre!

200
00:08:56,833 --> 00:08:58,416
And I skipped lunch
for fifteen days

201
00:08:58,500 --> 00:09:00,666
just to be able to
support their noble cause!

202
00:09:00,750 --> 00:09:03,708
[sobs]

203
00:09:03,791 --> 00:09:05,500
I get it, okay?

204
00:09:05,583 --> 00:09:06,750
Here!

205
00:09:06,833 --> 00:09:10,375
[JUNICHIRO gasps] A new
copy of Battle World 3!

206
00:09:10,458 --> 00:09:13,541
Uh. Why do you
have this?

207
00:09:13,625 --> 00:09:14,833
[MADOKA]
Because KMC

208
00:09:14,916 --> 00:09:17,458
just happens to be
my family's company!

209
00:09:17,541 --> 00:09:19,208
[gasps]

210
00:09:19,291 --> 00:09:20,708
[JUNICHIRO]
What?!

211
00:09:20,791 --> 00:09:22,708
You're telling me that's
the family business

212
00:09:22,791 --> 00:09:24,208
you're supposed to inherit?

213
00:09:24,291 --> 00:09:25,416
[MADOKA] Sure is.

214
00:09:25,500 --> 00:09:27,583
Remember when I told
you it was my birthday?

215
00:09:27,666 --> 00:09:29,166
My family has a tradition.

216
00:09:29,250 --> 00:09:32,000
When a child reaches sixteen,
he or she must find a partner

217
00:09:32,083 --> 00:09:33,250
who will help support them

218
00:09:33,333 --> 00:09:35,875
so they can take over
the business together.

219
00:09:35,958 --> 00:09:37,500
[gasps]

220
00:09:37,583 --> 00:09:39,208
Well? It's my turn today,

221
00:09:39,291 --> 00:09:41,666
and I'd heard an
awful lot about you.

222
00:09:41,750 --> 00:09:44,166
It didn't really hit me
until I saw you in person,

223
00:09:44,250 --> 00:09:46,000
but... now I know.

224
00:09:46,083 --> 00:09:47,125
Yeah?

225
00:09:47,208 --> 00:09:49,125
You are the only one for me!

226
00:09:49,208 --> 00:09:50,791
If I can have you by my side,

227
00:09:50,875 --> 00:09:52,750
then there's nothing
we can't accomplish!

228
00:09:52,833 --> 00:09:54,666
Just think! We could
make video games

229
00:09:54,750 --> 00:09:56,541
that the whole world
would want to play!

230
00:09:56,625 --> 00:09:58,625
[grunts]

231
00:09:58,708 --> 00:10:00,541
What d'you say?

232
00:10:00,625 --> 00:10:04,583
I know it's sudden, but I'm
not such a bad catch, am I?

233
00:10:04,666 --> 00:10:05,625
[grunts]

234
00:10:09,916 --> 00:10:13,416
I'm sorry, but you barely
know anything about me.

235
00:10:13,500 --> 00:10:15,041
And getting married
without building up

236
00:10:15,125 --> 00:10:18,166
any relationship points would
lead us both to the bad ending.

237
00:10:18,250 --> 00:10:19,791
Besides, if I'm not mistaken,

238
00:10:19,875 --> 00:10:21,583
your company's up
in the Hills, right?

239
00:10:21,666 --> 00:10:23,958
No way I could live in
such an uptight place.

240
00:10:24,041 --> 00:10:27,208
I'd probably suffocate within
thirty seconds of being there.

241
00:10:27,291 --> 00:10:28,583
See ya later!

242
00:10:30,916 --> 00:10:31,875
[grunts]

243
00:10:52,916 --> 00:10:54,791
[CROWD cheers]

244
00:10:54,875 --> 00:10:55,833
[GATES]
Hmph.

245
00:11:00,083 --> 00:11:01,125
[CROWD cheers]

246
00:11:01,208 --> 00:11:02,750
[ANNOUNCER]
You saw it coming, folks!

247
00:11:02,833 --> 00:11:06,166
He has overpowered his opponents
and claimed the championship

248
00:11:06,250 --> 00:11:08,250
title for the third
year in a row!

249
00:11:08,333 --> 00:11:11,541
Your winner is Hell Gates!

250
00:11:21,166 --> 00:11:23,416
[BODYGU ARD] It seems the
situation has come to a head.

251
00:11:23,500 --> 00:11:25,000
I see.

252
00:11:25,083 --> 00:11:28,666
I suppose I have no choice but
