they'll fire every one

504
00:20:51,708 --> 00:20:54,208
of our workers without
a second thought.

505
00:20:54,291 --> 00:20:55,916
This is exactly what my parents

506
00:20:56,000 --> 00:20:58,958
were getting ready for when they
trained me in housekeepin'.

507
00:20:59,041 --> 00:21:03,375
So, no, I don't have any
choice in the matter.

508
00:21:03,458 --> 00:21:05,458
Now do you see?

509
00:21:05,541 --> 00:21:06,708
That's why...

510
00:21:09,500 --> 00:21:12,791
I literally know
how much I'm worth.

511
00:21:12,875 --> 00:21:14,958
Sorry I kept this from you.

512
00:21:15,041 --> 00:21:16,833
I didn't want you to have
any reason to doubt my

513
00:21:16,916 --> 00:21:18,500
feelings were true.

514
00:21:18,583 --> 00:21:21,416
Because I really would
like to marry you.

515
00:21:21,500 --> 00:21:23,208
Call me a coward.

516
00:21:24,666 --> 00:21:26,875
[MADOKA] I figured if
I had you by my side.

517
00:21:26,958 --> 00:21:29,000
I could make all my
dreams come true.

518
00:21:29,083 --> 00:21:32,250
But sometimes you've
got to wake up, right?

519
00:21:32,333 --> 00:21:33,791
[MADOKA gasps]

520
00:21:33,875 --> 00:21:36,958
Don't act like you
know everything, Money Bags.

521
00:21:37,041 --> 00:21:39,333
I'm not letting you
go out on that note.

522
00:21:39,416 --> 00:21:41,958
[MADOKA]
Uh... Huh?

523
00:21:42,041 --> 00:21:45,416
Heh. The survival of a video
game company relies solely

524
00:21:45,500 --> 00:21:48,041
on an inter-corporate
political marriage?

525
00:21:48,125 --> 00:21:49,541
They make summer blockbusters

526
00:21:49,625 --> 00:21:52,833
about that kind of
crazy situation.

527
00:21:52,916 --> 00:21:56,750
And yet, the plot has
only begun to thicken!

528
00:23:30,500 --> 00:23:32,958
[MADOKA] Hey, all,
this is Madoka Kuramochi!

529
00:23:33,041 --> 00:23:35,875
I've never met anyone
like Mr. Kagami before.

530
00:23:35,958 --> 00:23:37,541
That's why he's so attractive.

531
00:23:37,625 --> 00:23:38,666
Next episode,

532
00:23:38,750 --> 00:23:40,958
genius programmer
Hell Gates arrives!

533
00:23:41,041 --> 00:23:42,791
Wait, what's he doing here?

534
00:23:42,875 --> 00:23:45,541
Mr. Kagami, you can't
make a promise like that!

535
00:23:45,625 --> 00:23:47,291
You had better have a plan!

536
00:23:47,375 --> 00:23:50,333
Period Fifteen,
"The Fiancé is a Game King."

537
00:23:50,416 --> 00:23:52,375
You need to take
this seriously!

538
00:23:52,458 --> 00:23:53,750
But I hope you win.

539
00:23:53,833 --> 00:23:56,416
I really don't want to marry
someone I don't love.

